Class DataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jdbdt.DataSet
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TypedDataSet

    public class DataSet
extends Object
    Data set.

    A data set represents a collection of database rows.

    Since:
    1.0

      • isReadOnly

        public final boolean isReadOnly()
        Check if the data set is read-only.

        Adding rows to a read-only data set will result in an exception of type InvalidOperationException.

        Returns:
        true if data set is read-only.
        See Also:
        setReadOnly()

      • setReadOnly

        public final void setReadOnly()
        Set data set as read-only.

        Adding rows to a read-only data set will result in an exception of type InvalidOperationException. The read-only setting cannot be disabled after this method is called.

        See Also:
        isReadOnly()
